      "@supabase/auth-js.GoTrueAdminApi.createUser": {
        "comment": {
          "examples": [
            {
              "code": "\`\`\`js
const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.admin.createUser({
  email: 'user@email.com',
  password: 'password',
  user_metadata: { name: 'Yoda' }
})
\`\`\`",
              "data": undefined,
              "description": undefined,
              "id": "with-custom-user-metadata",
              "name": "With custom user metadata",
              "response": "\`\`\`json
{
  data: {
    user: {
      id: '1',
      aud: 'authenticated',
      role: 'authenticated',
      email: 'example@email.com',
      email_confirmed_at: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z',
      phone: '',
      confirmation_sent_at: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z',
      confirmed_at: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z',
      last_sign_in_at: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z',
      app_metadata: {},
      user_metadata: {},
      identities: [
        {
          "identity_id": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
          "id": "1",
          "user_id": "1",
          "identity_data": {
            "email": "example@email.com",
            "email_verified": true,
            "phone_verified": false,
            "sub": "1"
          },
          "provider": "email",
          "last_sign_in_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z",
          "created_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z",
          "updated_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z",
          "email": "email@example.com"
        },
      ],
      created_at: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z',
      updated_at: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z',
      is_anonymous: false,
    }
  }
  error: null
}
\`\`\`",
            },
            {
              "code": "\`\`\`js
const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.admin.createUser({
  email: 'user@email.com',
  email_confirm: true
})
\`\`\`",
              "data": undefined,
              "description": undefined,
              "id": "auto-confirm-the-user-s-email",
              "name": "Auto-confirm the user's email",
              "response": undefined,
            },
            {
              "code": "\`\`\`js
const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.admin.createUser({
  phone: '1234567890',
  phone_confirm: true
})
\`\`\`",
              "data": undefined,
              "description": undefined,
              "id": "auto-confirm-the-user-s-phone-number",
              "name": "Auto-confirm the user's phone number",
              "response": undefined,
            },
          ],
          "shortText": "Creates a new user.
This function should only be called on a server. Never expose your \`service_role\` key in the browser.",
          "text": "- To confirm the user's email address or phone number, set \`email_confirm\` or \`phone_confirm\` to true. Both arguments default to false.
- \`createUser()\` will not send a confirmation email to the user. You can use [\`inviteUserByEmail()\`](/docs/reference/javascript/auth-admin-inviteuserbyemail) if you want to send them an email invite instead.
- If you are sure that the created user's email or phone number is legitimate and verified, you can set the \`email_confirm\` or \`phone_confirm\` param to \`true\`.",
        },
        "name": "@supabase/auth-js.GoTrueAdminApi.createUser",
        "params": [
          {
            "name": "attributes",
            "type": {
              "name": "AdminUserAttributes",
              "properties": [
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "A custom data object to store the user's application specific metadata. This maps to the \`auth.users.app_metadata\` column.

Only a service role can modify.

The \`app_metadata\` should be a JSON object that includes app-specific info, such as identity providers, roles, and other
access control information.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "app_metadata",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "object",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "Determines how long a user is banned for.

The format for the ban duration follows a strict sequence of decimal numbers with a unit suffix.
Valid time units are "ns", "us" (or "µs"), "ms", "s", "m", "h".

For example, some possible durations include: '300ms', '2h45m'.

Setting the ban duration to 'none' lifts the ban on the user.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "ban_duration",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's current password

This is only ever present when the user is resetting
their password and GOTRUE_SECURITY_UPDATE_PASSWORD_REQUIRE_CURRENT_PASSWORD is true.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "current_password",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's email.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "email",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "Sets the user's email as confirmed when true, or unconfirmed when false.

Only a service role can modify.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "email_confirm",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "boolean",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The \`id\` for the user.

Allows you to overwrite the default \`id\` set for the user.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "id",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The nonce sent for reauthentication if the user's password is to be updated.

Call reauthenticate() to obtain the nonce first.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "nonce",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's password.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "password",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The \`password_hash\` for the user's password.

Allows you to specify a password hash for the user. This is useful for migrating a user's password hash from another service.

Supports bcrypt, scrypt (firebase), and argon2 password hashes.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "password_hash",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's phone.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "phone",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "Sets the user's phone as confirmed when true, or unconfirmed when false.

Only a service role can modify.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "phone_confirm",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "boolean",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The \`role\` claim set in the user's access token JWT.

When a user signs up, this role is set to \`authenticated\` by default. You should only modify the \`role\` if you need to provision several levels of admin access that have different permissions on individual columns in your database.

Setting this role to \`service_role\` is not recommended as it grants the user admin privileges.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "role",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "A custom data object to store the user's metadata. This maps to the \`auth.users.raw_user_meta_data\` column.


The \`user_metadata\` should be a JSON object that includes user-specific info, such as their first and last name.

Note: When using the GoTrueAdminApi and wanting to modify a user's metadata,
this attribute is used instead of UserAttributes data.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "user_metadata",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "object",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
              ],
              "type": "object",
            },
          },
        ],
