          "shortText": "Updates the user data. Changes are applied directly without confirmation flows.",
          "text": "**Important:** This is a server-side operation and does **not** trigger client-side
\`onAuthStateChange\` listeners. The admin API has no connection to client state.

To sync changes to the client after calling this method:
1. On the client, call \`supabase.auth.refreshSession()\` to fetch the updated user data
2. This will trigger the \`TOKEN_REFRESHED\` event and notify all listeners",
        },
        "name": "@supabase/auth-js.GoTrueAdminApi.updateUserById",
        "params": [
          {
            "comment": {
              "shortText": "The user's unique identifier",
            },
            "name": "uid",
            "type": {
              "name": "string",
              "type": "intrinsic",
            },
          },
          {
            "comment": {
              "shortText": "The data you want to update.

This function should only be called on a server. Never expose your \`service_role\` key in the browser.",
            },
            "name": "attributes",
            "type": {
              "name": "AdminUserAttributes",
              "properties": [
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "A custom data object to store the user's application specific metadata. This maps to the \`auth.users.app_metadata\` column.

Only a service role can modify.

The \`app_metadata\` should be a JSON object that includes app-specific info, such as identity providers, roles, and other
access control information.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "app_metadata",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "object",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "Determines how long a user is banned for.

The format for the ban duration follows a strict sequence of decimal numbers with a unit suffix.
Valid time units are "ns", "us" (or "µs"), "ms", "s", "m", "h".

For example, some possible durations include: '300ms', '2h45m'.

Setting the ban duration to 'none' lifts the ban on the user.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "ban_duration",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's current password

This is only ever present when the user is resetting
their password and GOTRUE_SECURITY_UPDATE_PASSWORD_REQUIRE_CURRENT_PASSWORD is true.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "current_password",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's email.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "email",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "Sets the user's email as confirmed when true, or unconfirmed when false.

Only a service role can modify.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "email_confirm",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "boolean",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The \`id\` for the user.

Allows you to overwrite the default \`id\` set for the user.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "id",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The nonce sent for reauthentication if the user's password is to be updated.

Call reauthenticate() to obtain the nonce first.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "nonce",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's password.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "password",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The \`password_hash\` for the user's password.

Allows you to specify a password hash for the user. This is useful for migrating a user's password hash from another service.

Supports bcrypt, scrypt (firebase), and argon2 password hashes.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "password_hash",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The user's phone.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "phone",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "Sets the user's phone as confirmed when true, or unconfirmed when false.

Only a service role can modify.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "phone_confirm",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "boolean",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "The \`role\` claim set in the user's access token JWT.

When a user signs up, this role is set to \`authenticated\` by default. You should only modify the \`role\` if you need to provision several levels of admin access that have different permissions on individual columns in your database.

Setting this role to \`service_role\` is not recommended as it grants the user admin privileges.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "role",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "string",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
                {
                  "comment": {
                    "shortText": "A custom data object to store the user's metadata. This maps to the \`auth.users.raw_user_meta_data\` column.


The \`user_metadata\` should be a JSON object that includes user-specific info, such as their first and last name.

Note: When using the GoTrueAdminApi and wanting to modify a user's metadata,
this attribute is used instead of UserAttributes data.",
                  },
                  "isOptional": true,
                  "name": "user_metadata",
                  "type": {
                    "name": "object",
                    "type": "intrinsic",
                  },
                },
              ],
              "type": "object",
            },
          },
        ],
